5:
Oh, so that's what happened with
House Tris. I see...
9:
I see that you are out of your mind!
We're talking about a high-ranking
priest who spends more money
than he has on women and drinks!
13:
Thanks for covering me, Libram.
Don't worry, I'll repay my debts
someday!
18:
If you've come here with useful
information, I'd be glad to repay the
debt you have with my brother. Now,
would you tell me more?
22:
Within Oxtan territory, there is a
research facility which, presumably,
the Star Augurs have something to
do with.
25:
On paper, they are researching
relics. But the flow of money and
people to and from it makes me
believe otherwise.
27:
We must find what they are using all
these mysterious funds for.
32:
...Assuming they haven't covered
their tracks already, like a lizard
abandoning its tail.
35:
I hear the Star Augurs are
exceptionally good at that. It doesn't
help the family involved is only a
branch family from the outskirts.
37:
So in other words, the lizard will still
escape unscathed even if we cut its
tail.
42:
A lizard can regrow its tail, but make
no mistake. Having it cut definitely
hurts!
44:
And, even if we cannot uncover the
whole conspiracy, it will be enough
to make some noise. Wouldn't you
say that's useful in and of itself?
50:
I understand. At times like this, an
unflattering truth about a branch
family could be enough.
52:
But... you do not seem convinced,
Your Highness.
56:
Correct me if I'm wrong, but... the
idea is to threaten House Oxtan into
silence so that they can no longer
hinder us, is it not?
61:
Indeed. It is the fastest and most
logical course of action.
66: I see. In that case, I'm against it.
69:
We know that Palpebra has no ill
intent against us.
72:
If so, we should be able to persuade
everyone without resorting to
threats! Our truth and justice should
be enough to convince them to help
the people!
76:
It was not enough to convince
House Tris.
80:
Still! If we persevere long enough,
eventually, they will listen.
83:
Surely you agree, Yuwel? As a
Swallow Knight, you must
understand where I'm coming from!
88: I am terribly sorry, Your Highness.
91:
I could not blindly follow my ideals.
Nor do I believe that doing so now
would be of any use.
93:
Sometimes, one must resign himself
to fight through the mud. Even if one
must yield, even if one must lose...
96:
I see the priest's proposal as the first
step. Please, Your Highness, believe
in me and lend us your aid.
104:
So, is it true that he's investigating
the Kweturs and Oxtans?
107:
Sure is. We met while they were tryin'
to settle things with Orgus. He ain't
taking this lightly, believe me.
109: He even knew that I'm Velgar Oinas.
113:
Did you tell him the truth about what
happened thirty years ago with the
assassination of Princess Etheria?
116:
Ain't no way. The truth would've
shocked 'im dead.
119:
Mutual interest brings us together.
No more, no less. In the end, he's an
Oxtan. When the time comes, I'll be
burnin' that bridge.
123: Oh. No more, no less, huh?
130:
What are you people doin' then? Yer
just going to let that royal brat do as
he pleases? That's some risk right
there!
134:
As far as Prince Varen goes... There's
not much we can do.
137:
But he'll be fine. He has the Swallow
Knight with him after all.
143:
Thank you for coming despite the
situation. I absolutely needed to
speak with you.
146:
I must apologize, Yuwel. I was
forcing the expectations of my
haughty ideals on you!
149:
I was moved by the Swallow Knights.
I wanted to follow the ideal of those
who gave their life for a cause!
153:
But, when faced with reality, there is
no such thing as a noble defeat.
That is what I have now realized. Is
that not the case? What do you
think?
157:
Wh-what do I think? Is th-that what
you wanted to speak to me about?
161:
Indeed! I thought long and hard
about what you and Cieldeau said
to me.
163:
I want to know how you can keep
fighting through such a muddy path
and push onward.
167:
You are incredible... In a few hours,
you understood what took me a
whole year.
170:
It is simple, Your Highness. You just
need to listen. Listen to those who
keep struggling despite walking in
the mud.
172:
Because even when one forsakes
his role as a knight to become a
shop owner, or even a cook, one can
still find light in their path.
175:
Shop owner or cook? What are you
talking about?
179:
Allow me to share a tale from some
time ago...
183:
So, you never returned home to
House Nouin?
186:
Ashamed as I am to admit it, I have
not. And Ciel reprimanded me for it.
188:
I couldn't have been further from my
ideals. I even ran from my own
brothers, instead of facing them.
192: I wonder if what I did was the same...
194:
Talking is all it takes. That's what my
father, the King's brother, used to
say.
197:
But one day, he stopped saying that
and he stopped speaking of ideals.
So...
200:
I see now. I should've listened then
too, right?
203:
Yes... I am sure that listening is the
answer.
205:
And that means what we must do
should be clear.
210:
Of course! Let's go see what the
Oxtans have to say !
